  "texts": [
    "This behavior aligns with observations in traditional Transformer models, as exemplified by Qwen's attention maps such as AL24 and AL27.",
    "Decrease of attention to vision tokens across layers.Comparing the second row with the first row in Figure 8, we observe a clear downward trend in attention scores assigned to vision tokens as the layers deepen.",
    "This phenomenon is consistent with our broader findings: as the model processes more layers, visual information becomes increasingly redundant and is subsequently deprioritized by instruction and response tokens.",
    "Qualitative results.",
    "Figure 9 illustrates qualitative examples from MCQ, TVG, and VDC tasks."
  ]
